The Pistons are continuing their effort to help the city of Detroit in the fight against COVID-19.
The Pistons announced Monday that team owner Tom Gores is buying 100,000 surgical-grade masks, which will be distributed by medical workers, first responders and other essential city workers on the front lines during the coronavirus pandemic.
Tom Gores (Photo: Robin Buckson, Detroit News)“First responders and city workers are on the front line of this crisis and they need our support now more than ever,” Gores said in a statement.
“Once we get past the immediate threat from the virus, there will be so much more to do,” Gores said.
“We need plans to revitalize the economy, which will help struggling families and programs to make sure kids aren’t set behind.